			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">don't worry about raid, there is really no reason for you to be using it.
<br />

<br />
also, as to the HyperThreading issue...i could be wrong, but i could've sworn the AMD chips did have their version of dual threading.  i don't think any of the XP's do, but eh, i'm out of date so who the hell knows.
<br />

<br />
since you are going to be building a new computer, something fun to do with your old one is turn it into a DVR and HDTV box.  There are a number of video cards that are HDTV (and digital TV, and even satellite) compatible.  I don't remember which off hand.  Both ATI and Nvidia make a video card that is a basic tuner.
<br />

<br />
That is what i'm going to do with my old box whenever i upgrade.  get a card that can do HD and use it for overair HD (i'll probably look for a directv compatible one so i can use it as a DVR for normal TV...but it all depends on cost).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
