			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi all, me again...
<br />

<br />
Raid - Yes it's usefull, in every situation? - umm.. not.  Artisbull hit it on the head, it's about data transfer rates.  How much of the zone info is stored on your HD vs how much do you get from Sony.  Sony only tells location information, the rest  of the info sits on your computer.  A raid set up will speed up your zoning time, and &lt;&lt;guessing here&gt;&gt; should give you less of a chance to crash while zoning because you aren't going to have as much of a lag issue with Sony over the internet while your system searches for the info to load the zone.  Now the real question is - Is this extra bit of stability worth the $100 to $200 extra dollars you'll pay per HD for getting the extra HD(s) to get a Raid configuration set-up.  
<br />

<br />
Please note - there are multiple Raid configurations - not just Raid and non Raid.  Conceivably you could have a 6 harddrives running 1 set of data.  (Trust me on this or look it up yourself).
<br />

<br />
6800 vs 9500 - Enable every bloody feature and then go POK and watch a crowd get multiple MGB's.... that's when you'll see the differnence.  Essentially it's the difference between looking up at 2 mountains from the base.  One is 1000 ft high and another is 2000 ft high.  You won't be able to tell jack from your perspective because the average amount of rendering can be done by both cards equally well... but when you need that extra bit of processing for extreme amounts of info, then the difference becomes apparant.
<br />

<br />
Ram - 2700 vs 3200 - get the 3200. For the extra $5, get the faster timings already and stop worrying about it.  Your time is worth more than the explanation to understand latencies, RAS charge, delays and lookup tables.  Also try to get 512 MB Minimum with any current system but I'd recommend 1 GB.
<br />

<br />
If you want to find a reputable source near you and your not that technically inclined - look up the newsgroups for your local city - and just ask for 2 things.  Which places to avoid and which places people would recommend.  Avoid any place on the first list even if it appears on the second list.  Now you've got a few choices.  And buying a computer when your not technically inclined is like prison rape, your just getting to choose your cell mate this time.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy guys - and if you really want to have fun - try playing a game of "Lick the electrical socket"  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="Twisted Evil" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Death chases you like Night chases Day</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
